# Linear Workflow Rules

Use this rule when a task involves Linear, issue tracking, roadmap slicing, or delivery reporting.

1. Prefer a one-issue-at-a-time implementation style.
2. Map each work slice to one of the prepared backlog groups in `docs/linear-integration.md`.
3. If the active session has live Linear tools, read/update the Linear issue before and after major code changes.
4. If live Linear tools are unavailable, update local docs instead:
   - `docs/project-status-roadmap.md`
   - `docs/reports/*.md`
   - `docs/exports/linear-import-roadmap.csv`
5. Branch naming convention when issue keys are known:
   - `reallystate/<ISSUE-KEY>-short-slug`
   - `codex/<ISSUE-KEY>-short-slug`
6. Commit message convention when issue keys are known:
   - `<ISSUE-KEY>: short summary`
7. Do not mark work complete in Linear or the local roadmap unless tests or verification for that slice actually passed.
